articles.author: James Mackenzie, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Israel said on Sunday it was delaying the release of hundreds of Palestinian prisoners it had planned to free the day before until militant group Hamas met its conditions, underscoring the fragility of the Gaza ceasefire accord.
articles.title: Israel says it is postponing release of Palestinian prisoners

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hamas on Sunday condemned Israel's decision to postpone the release of Palestinian prisoners and detainees, saying its claim that the hostages' handover ceremonies are "humiliating" was false and a pretext to evade Israel's obligations under the Gaza ceasefire agreement.
articles.title: Hamas says Israel's claim on hostages' handover ceremony is pretext to evade its obligations

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Pope Francis, who is battling double pneumonia in hospital, had a "tranquil" night and rested, the Vatican said on Sunday.
articles.title: Pope Francis had 'tranquil' night in hospital, Vatican says

articles.author: Sarah Marsh
articles.description: The far-right AfD likely will score its best ever result as Europe's ailing economic powerhouse lurches rightwards. The conservative CDU/CSU bloc is set to win, but will be unlikely to secure a majority.
articles.title: Gloomy Germans vote in election which conservatives are set to win

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia launched several waves of missile and drone attacks overnight targeting Kyiv and other parts of Ukraine, killing one civilian in Kryvyi Rih and damaging buildings and cars in Kyiv and elsewhere, officials said early on Sunday.
articles.title: Russian attacks kill one in Kryvyi Rih, damage houses in Kyiv, Ukraine officials say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Tens of thousands of people gathered on the outskirts of Beirut on Sunday to pay their respects to Hezbollah's slain leader Hassan Nasrallah, nearly five months after he was killed in an Israeli airstrike in a stunning blow to the Iran-backed group.
articles.title: Tens of thousands mourn Hezbollah's slain leader Nasrallah in mass funeral

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China defence ministry spokesperson Wu Qian said on Sunday that Australian complaints over recent Chinese live-fire naval drills in international waters between Australia and New Zealand were "hyped up" and "inconsistent with the facts".
articles.title: China accuses Australia of 'hyping' Chinese naval drills

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Switzerland could contribute troops to a future peacekeeping mission in Ukraine if it were requested and the government agreed, Swiss armed forces chief Thomas Suessli said in an interview published on Sunday.
articles.title: Swiss could contribute to peacekeeping in Ukraine, army chief says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov will visit Turkey on Monday to discuss his country's recent talks with U.S. officials on ending the war in Ukraine, and how Ankara can contribute to the process, a Turkish foreign ministry source said on Sunday.
articles.title: Russia's Lavrov to discuss Turkish role in ending Ukraine war in visit, source says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Swiss police have arrested a 28-year-old Australian man suspected of stabbing and seriously injuring a 41-year-old man in a shop in central Zurich, authorities said.
articles.title: Swiss police arrest Australian man over stabbing in Zurich
